Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks. Pop 
them on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and 
@ground black pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer and 
roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}, 
turning halfway.

Meanwhile, arrange the @cauliflower florets{300%g} on another baking tray. 
> Halve any large pieces. Tip: Add less Chermoula spice mix if you don't like 
> too much heat. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and the 
@Chermoula spice mix{1%tsp}. Use your hands to rub the seasoning all over. 
Arrange in a single layer and roast on the middle shelf of your oven until 
soft and golden at the edges, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While the potatoes and cauli cook, heat a splash of @oil{} in a large 
#frying pan{} over high heat. When hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g}, 
season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and cook until the chicken is 
browned, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn every couple of mins to make sure the chicken 
cooks evenly. Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{80%g} and chop into thirds, 
halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}.

Once the chicken is browned, add the green beans and shallot to the chicken 
pan. Stir-fry until the chicken is cooked through, the beans are tender, and 
shallot is soft, another ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked through when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the roast potatoes to the frying pan with the chicken and stir in the 
@harissa paste{50%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute}. Remove from the heat and make 
sure the chicken and veggies are nicely coated in the harissa paste. Season to 
taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Share the chicken, beans and potatoes between your plates. Pop the cauliflower 
pieces on top. Drizzle over the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} and enjoy!